title: Sources: Udoka joins tier of top-paid coaches
description: Rockets coach Ime Udoka has agreed to a long-term contract extension that makes him one of the highest-paid coaches in the NBA, sources told ESPN.
author: Shams Charania

title: QB Sanders cited twice this month for speeding
description: Shedeur Sanders, who was stopped for an alleged speeding violation Tuesday, also was cited for speeding earlier this month, according to court records.
author: ESPN News Services

title: 'Touched by God' - Messi shows he still has magic touch
description: Few things are as inevitable as the ball hitting the back of the net when Lionel Messi sizes up the target before executing a free-kick from 20 yards.

title: 'This is it - time for England to be winners'
description: England's series against India, which begins on Friday, starts a era-defining 10-game spell for captain Ben Stokes and coach Brendon McCullum, writes chief cricket reporter Stephan Shemilt.

title: Is Aaron Rodgers 'In The Best Shape'?
description: Super Bowl champion Phil Simms believes Aaron Rodgers will come up big for the Pittsburgh Steelers this season.

title: Schwarber hits 23rd homer of season, Sánchez pitches 8 sharp innings to lead Phillies past Marlins
description: Kyle Schwarber hit a tiebreaking solo home run in the eighth, Christopher Sánchez pitched eight sharp innings and the Philadelphia Phillies beat the Miami Marlins 2-1 on Thursday night. Sánchez (6-2) allowed five hits, one run and struck out four. Philadelphia took three of four in the series.
author: ALANIS THAMES

title: Premier League fixtures: Man Utd host Arsenal on bumper opening weekend
description: Manchester United host Arsenal in the first Super Sunday of the 2025/26 Premier League season, with Liverpool, Manchester City, Chelsea and FA Cup winners Crystal Palace also featuring live on Sky Sports on a bumper opening weekend.

title: Leverkusen close to Quansah agreement as Wirtz flies in to seal £100m Reds move
description: Bayer Leverkusen are in advanced negotiations with Liverpool to sign defender Jarell Quansah, while the Bundesliga club's playmaker Florian Wirtz arrived in the UK on Thursday evening to complete his £100m move to the Premier League champions.
